Which statement is true about HP Web Jetadmin plug-ins?
A. Plug-ins are hardware modules that can be added to an HP LaserJet.
B. Plug-ins are special scripts that can be sent to the printer by HP Web Jetadmin.
C. Plug-ins are DIMMs that add functionality to the printer when accessed by HP Web
Jetadmin.
D. Plug-ins are software packages that add extra functionality to the HP Web Jetadmin
application
Answer: D
What determines the extent to which HP Web Jetadmin can manage third-party printers?
A. WMI
B. DMI
C. MIB
D. SNMP
Answer: D
Reference:http://bizsupport1.austin.hp.com/bc/docs/support/SupportManual/c01675324/c0
1675324.pdf(page 2, Discovering devices, second paragraph)
Which commands apply to SNMPv2?
A. set and getnext
B. getbulk and inform
C. trap and set
D. trap and getnext
Answer: A
